Command                           Description                                           Example
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ps                                Display a snapshot of current processes.              ps
ps -e                             Display all processes.                                ps -e
ps -f                             Display full-format listing.                          ps -f
ps -u username                    Display processes for a specific user.                ps -u john
ps -p pid                         Display information for a specific process ID.        ps -p 1234
ps aux                            Display detailed information about all processes.     ps aux
ps -ef                            Display all processes in full-format listing.         ps -ef
ps -eo pid,ppid,cmd,%mem,%cpu    Display custom format output.                         ps -eo pid,ppid,cmd,%mem,%cpu
ps -C cmd                         Display processes by command name.                    ps -C nginx
ps --sort=-%mem                   Display processes sorted by memory usage.             ps --sort=-%mem
